        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 4:41PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 441 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a shower near Albuquerque,
moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Albuquerque, Tijeras, Cedar Crest, North Valley, South Valley,
Sandia Park, Carnuel, Cedro and Canoncito in Bernalillo County.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 157 and 176.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 215 and 229.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
